Bielecki Says Poland Won’t Use Tax Increases to Boost Revenue

-- B y   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 
2011-10-10T08:21:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/bielecki-says-poland-won-t-use-tax-increases-to-boost-revenue.html
Poland’s government won’t raise
taxes to increase revenue, Jan Krzysztof Bielecki, head of Prime
Minister Donald Tusk’s council of economic advisers, said in an
interview on TVN CNBC television today, as voting returns showed
the government was headed toward re-election.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nathaniel Espino at 
 nespino@bloomberg.net  